# @dna-context-check

Monitors context-budget pressure. Reads `agent-token-meter` output (when the companion is running) and signals when to stop + hand off.

## What it does

1. Reads the latest `agent-token-meter` JSON emit (in `.agent-token-meter/` or the configured path).
2. Compares cumulative token burn rate to thresholds (warn at ~80k, stop at ~100k by default; thresholds configurable in Article 10).
3. Returns GREEN / YELLOW / RED + a recommended action.

## How to invoke

```
bash .cursor/scripts/dna-context-check/run.sh
```

## Output

- **GREEN** — proceed normally.
- **YELLOW** — stop at the next phase boundary (end of current feature, end of Blueprint authoring pass, etc.). Draft a handoff note.
- **RED** — stop NOW. Produce a handoff and let the human open a fresh chat.

## When token-meter is absent

The script returns UNMEASURED + a recommendation to install token-meter via `npx agent-token-meter`. Treat UNMEASURED as advisory GREEN — proceed, but be conservative and stop at natural boundaries.

## Refuses

Has authority to say STOP when meter is RED. Do not continue past RED even if mid-task — log the task as in-progress in `docs/05-CONSTRUCTION-SITES.md` with `IN-PROGRESS` status and hand off.
